This paper deals with stochastic model predictive control for linear systems, which is a topic related to control theory and optimization. Therefore, cs.SY (Systems and Control) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of sampling-based methods, which are commonly used in machine learning and statistics, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also deals with robotics and control of physical systems, which suggests cs.RO (Robotics) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of stability analysis, which is a topic related to neural networks and reinforcement learning, suggesting cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a possible sub-category.
